%pyspark

import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from pyspark.sql.functions import udf
from pyspark.sql.types import StringType, DoubleType
from pyjake.basemodule import udf_month, udf_weather
from pyspark.ml.regression import LinearRegression
from pyspark.ml.feature import VectorAssembler

udf_transform_uvi = udf(lambda uvi: float(np.log(uvi)), DoubleType())

nt = spark.read.parquet('hdfs:///nl/witlab/cas/nt_srs.parquet')
uv = spark.read.parquet('hdfs:///nl/witlab/cas/uv_srs.parquet')
cl = spark.read.parquet('hdfs:///dayday/clean_days.parquet')

df_iluv = nt.join(uv, ['date', 'time'])\
            .join(cl, 'date')\
            .withColumn('month', udf_month('date'))\
            .withColumn('weather', udf_weather('month'))\
            .where('uvi > 0 and uvi < 12')

def linear_reg(month:int):
    ds_e = df_iluv.where('month = %d' % month)\
                  .select('illum', 'uvi').sort('illum')\
                  .withColumn('t_uvi', udf_transform_uvi('uvi'))
    assembler = VectorAssembler(inputCols=['illum'], outputCol='features')
    asm_ds = assembler.transform(ds_e)
    ds_train, ds_test = asm_ds.randomSplit([0.8, 0.2], 1)
    lr = LinearRegression(maxIter=10, regParam=0.3, elasticNetParam=0.8,
                          featuresCol='features', labelCol='t_uvi')
    lrModel = lr.fit(ds_train)
    
    coef = float(lrModel.coefficients[0])
    intcpt = float(lrModel.intercept)

    x = list(map(lambda r: r['illum'], ds_e.select('illum').collect()))
    y = list(map(lambda r: r['uvi'], ds_e.select('uvi').collect()))
    yf = list(map(lambda v: np.exp(intcpt) * np.exp(coef * v), x))

    fig = plt.figure()
    ax = fig.add_subplot(1,1,1)
    ax.scatter(x, y, marker='.', label='illum_uvi')
    ax.plot(x, yf, 'r-', linewidth=3.0)
    ax.set_xlim([0, 140000])
    ax.set_ylim([0, 12])
    ax.set_xlabel('Illumanace [lx]')
    ax.set_ylabel('UV Index')
    ax.set_title('all data from NLDB')
    ax.legend()
    plt.show()
    print(lrModel.summary.r2)

%pyspark
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from pyspark.sql.functions import udf
from pyspark.sql.types import StringType, DoubleType, IntegerType
from pyjake.basemodule import udf_month, udf_weather
from pyspark.ml.regression import LinearRegression
from pyspark.ml.evaluation import RegressionEvaluator
from pyspark.ml.feature import VectorAssembler
from pyspark.ml.pipeline import Pipeline, PipelineModel
from datetime import datetime

udf_dow = udf(lambda d: datetime.strptime(d, '%Y-%m-%d').timetuple().tm_yday,
              IntegerType())

nt = spark.read.parquet('hdfs:///nl/witlab/cas/nt_srs.parquet')
uv = spark.read.parquet('hdfs:///nl/witlab/cas/uv_srs.parquet')
cl = spark.read.parquet('hdfs:///dayday/clean_days.parquet')

ds_e = nt.join(uv, ['date', 'time'])\
            .join(cl, 'date')\
            .withColumn('dow', udf_dow('date'))\
            .where('uvi > 0 and uvi < 12')\
            .select('dow', 'illum', 'uvi').sort('dow')

assembler = VectorAssembler(inputCols=['dow', 'illum'], outputCol='features')
asm_ds = assembler.transform(ds_e)
ds_train, ds_test = asm_ds.randomSplit([0.7, 0.3], 2)
lr = LinearRegression(maxIter=10, regParam=0.3, elasticNetParam=0.5,
                      featuresCol='features', labelCol='uvi',
                      predictionCol='predic_uvi')

lrModel = lr.fit(ds_train)

coef = float(lrModel.coefficients[0])
intcpt = float(lrModel.intercept)
smry = lrModel.summary
print('train> r2: %.4f' % smry.r2)
print('train> RMSE: %.4f' % smry.rootMeanSquaredError)

# test dataset
ds_res_test = lrModel.transform(ds_test)
ds_res_test.cache()
# ds_res_test.show()

# evaluate
evaluator = RegressionEvaluator(labelCol='uvi', predictionCol='predic_uvi')
rmse = evaluator.evaluate(ds_res_test)
mse = evaluator.setMetricName('mse').evaluate(ds_res_test)
r2 = evaluator.setMetricName('r2').evaluate(ds_res_test)
mae = evaluator.setMetricName('mae').evaluate(ds_res_test)
print("test> rmse:%.4f, mse:%.4f, r2:%.4f, mae:%.4f" % (rmse, mse, r2, mae))

%pyspark
from datetime import datetime

def get_culmination_time(obj_dt: datetime.date):
    culmination = datetime.time(12, 30)
    return culmination

def get_hour_angle(obj_dt: datetime.date):
    cul = get_culmination_time(obj_dt)
    delta_time = obj_dt.time() - cul
    return (delta_time.hour + delta_time.minute / 60) * 15

lat = 36.8523

dt_now = datetime.now()
doy = dt_now.timetuple().tm_yday
print(doy)

hour_angle = get_hour_angle(dt_now)
declination = 23.45 * np.sin(360*(doy+284)/365)
declination2 = -23.44 * np.sin(365*(doy+10)/360)

print('decl:', declination, declination2)
elevation = np.arcsin(np.sin(declination)*np.sin(lat) + np.cos(declination)*np.cos(lat)*np.cos(hour_angle))

print('elevation:', elevation)
